cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about grounded language understanding, which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning models and their ability to generalize, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a synthetic VQA test, which involves computer vision, so it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
